      "writtenOn": "2018-05-23T02:49:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is the general pattern followed by all rules: they take a list of services (as IDs) the rule hits. \n\nBy default it uses whatever is defined in project(...) rule, so we don\u0027t have to repeat them all the time. But weird configs that use cr-buildbucket-test or cr-buildbucket-dev, etc. will be able to say so (albeit a bit more verbosely).",
